✅📱【Excellent External Storage For iPhone iPad】No need Internet or Wi-Fi any more.Using this iPhone usb drive, you can go on vacation or something and not have to worry about running out of space.You can play movies and music on this iPhone flash drive photo stick without taking up space on iPhone. The only setup that you need to do is install the "Y-DISK" app on your iPhone and plug in the iPhone storage device. Also You can save photos/videos direct to the photo stick via In-app camera.

✅📱【Priority to Privacy Protection】Compatible with iPhone photo stick to share files, photos and videos with colleagues and friends without worrying about personal privacy leaks. Media Formats Supported Music: M4A / AIFF / CAF / MP3 / WAV Image: GIF / JPG / PNG / JPEG Video: AVI / FLV / M4V / MKV / MOV / MP4 / RMVB Document: DOC / PPT / XLS / XLSX / PDF / HTML / TX

REMARKS 1. Flash drive for iPhone/iPad needs to download app ''Y-DISK'', you can search the app from the App Store. (When the phone does not recognize the usb stick, please uninstall the "Y-DISK" APP, then restart the phone and manually download the "Y-DISK" APP from the APP Store) 2. If you've used iCloud before to back up your files, you'll need to download the files from iCloud to your Phone or Pad and then copy them to usb flash drive. 3. For Android phones must have OTG function in order to use this flash drive, no need to download APP 4. Only support Android phones with OTG function. You can find the external usb storage in the "File Manager" APP of your phone. (NO NEED TO DOWNLOAD APP) * If your phone doesn't work, you need to open the phone set to open the OTG connection. PLEASE NOTE * You cannot transfer or view media files downloaded from iTunes or other third-party applications. Because these files are protected by digital rights management. * If necessary, please remove your phone case before use. Because the phone case will affect the connection between the phone and the usb flash drive. Even if you insert the usb drive into the phone, the usb drive may not be recognized by the phone. * The FAT32 format is usually suitable for small-capacity iphone flash drive and has better compatibility; if it is a large-capacity USB flash drive, the preferred format is recommended as: EXFAT>FAT32. If flash drive for iPhone cannot transfer files, you can convert FAT32 to EXFAT format by formatting. (Please save the file before formatting to prevent data loss) * After using the iPhone photo stick, please make sure to turn off the apps related to the iPhone flash drive, and then unplug the usb flash drive gently, so that the files in the usb flash drive will not be damaged.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Connectors don't connect.... sending it back
reviews.reviewText: I liked: I had trouble with scanning the QR so I searched for "Y disk" in my iphone apps and easily found the Y disk app. I noticed a very very low rating for the Y disk app/Y disk on the iphone app store. However, when I opened the app on my iphone, it was very easy to move all the photos from my phone to the app. The next step, attaching the actual device to my iphone, is where I ran into trouble.... see below.I didn't like: The connector for the iphone is way too short to fit either my iphone SE second generation, or an older iphone 11 pro. I read in other reviews that you have to take the case off in order to attach the device to the phones because it is too short. My cases are very hard to take off and this is not a good feature... a poorly designed, too small connector. Also, even with the iphone 11 pro outside it's case, the connector was not a good fit.... it was wobbly. Furthermore, after reading from another customer their concerns about attaching anything made in china to their computer, I decided that is the last straw..... I've worked for companies where we had corporate espionage by foreign actors from that country and it totally messed up all devices all employees had ever connected to their home office wifi, in addition to their work computers and work smart phones.Sending this back.Incidentally, the instruction manual is, as everyone else says, is way too small to be of any use other than to know what name to enter into an internet search, so you can pull up a manual on your laptop. I've found that more and more products, whether from apple, sandisk, or other tech companies, they don't even bother to put instructions in the box and you have to search for youtube videos or full manuals online. Advances in technology have resulted in poorer customer service in general. At least this company put a manual into the box, although that tiny print is a joke and is totally useless. I guess somewhat of "it's the thought that counts" was there.... maybe maybe.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 26, 2021
reviews.reviewText: I just received this in the mail today, I haven't got a chance to use it yet though. It seems to be made of super tough material and doesn't seem likely to fall apart! It comes with lots of instructions, A voucher for a extra free Flash drive, and a type C adapter end, all tucked away in a cute little Box, to keep it extra safe. I've had a couple of these over the years and I really love them, they come in hella handy! Now let's see if it passes the test of time, And doesn't crash or Completely quit working for no reason! Just a word of advice to anybody backing up anything of importance to these, always make sure you backup your important things to more than one place or thing. Because you never know When technology is gonna glitch! This was a damn good value for my money, hhopefully that doesn't bite me in the ass! Well if things go horribly wrong with this little device I'll be sure to update my review! But if everything turns out fine and dandy you won't hear for me again!
